                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.0144.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">O’Shaughnessy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-27T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul, Nuevo Laredo, and several citizens of Laredo, Texas, report to Department
                    that at nine o’clock last night Samuel Cantú, Mexican citizen, was kidnapped on
                    American side of international <pb facs="1017" n="901" xml:id="pg_901"/> bridge
                    between above two places, dragged across boundary and thrown into prison and it
                    is said that he is to be shot to-day.</p>
                <p>Say to appropriate authorities that, if facts are as stated, United States
                    Government demands immediate release of Cantu and his return to American side of
                    border.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
